<dl id="n08119b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08119b">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08119b"> 119(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> millstone <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n08119b"><li>FW 183.20 </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/lexg.htm#n08119b">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/l39g.htm#n08119b">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n08119b">MS BL 47474-11</ms> </li><li>JJA 47:370 <a name="gd2" href="../../ff/fdra/gda.htm#gd2">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/g/gd2.htm#n08119b">Draft: I.7&sect;1.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">She <font color="green">[the Holy Church]</font> is a lady, not a prude. Her inquisitions, her safeguards and indexes all aim at the avoidance of the scriptural millstone, which is so richly deserved by those who offend one of her little ones. <small> Shane Leslie (Domini Canis), <a name="ULY11" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ULY11"><cite title="source">&ldquo;Some Recent Books. Ulysses&rdquo;</cite></a>, <cite a>Dublin Review</cite></a> (Sep 1922) 113</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
